531
00:27:20,998 --> 00:27:22,709
Have you forgotten?
I live alone.

532
00:27:23,415 --> 00:27:26,072
Yeah, but only psycho chicks want to go to casa de killer.

533
00:27:41,920 --> 00:27:45,453
I need a job where I get paid to read the personals and drink slushies.

534
00:27:45,660 --> 00:27:46,480
You see this?

535
00:27:47,531 --> 00:27:48,563
It's about servando.

536
00:27:48,914 --> 00:27:51,322
If I die unexpectedly, do me a favor --

537
00:27:51,577 --> 00:27:54,929
go on "oprah" and tell the world I loved kittens.

538
00:27:56,386 --> 00:27:59,534
"Servando wept the first time he saw 'stand and deliver.'"

539
00:28:00,037 --> 00:28:01,360
Where do they even get that stuff?

540
00:28:01,574 --> 00:28:04,578
There was this new girl in class just soaking up the drama.

541
00:28:04,810 --> 00:28:07,187
She probably couldn't wait to talk to reporters.

542
00:28:14,356 --> 00:28:15,011
Yeah?

543
00:28:15,282 --> 00:28:17,741
Wait. Let me guess.
Save our beaches, right?

544
00:28:17,870 --> 00:28:19,088
- Jeff cotter?
- Yeah.

545
00:28:19,139 --> 00:28:20,007
My name is dawn --

546
00:28:20,179 --> 00:28:20,879
dawn lamb --

547
00:28:21,050 --> 00:28:22,690
assistant to the district attorney.

548
00:28:22,990 --> 00:28:24,495
Did you know ed doyle?

549
00:28:25,519 --> 00:28:28,749
Um, he was the bus driver in that accident, right?

550
00:28:28,800 --> 00:28:29,608
Yes.

551
00:28:29,872 --> 00:28:32,121
I've heard of him, you know, from the news.

552
00:28:32,431 --> 00:28:34,359
I think he lives around here, too.

553
00:28:34,468 --> 00:28:35,317
What's this about?

554
00:28:35,506 --> 00:28:39,116
Ed doyle placed a call from a convenience-store pay phone to your apartment

555
00:28:39,167 --> 00:28:41,779
about 15 minutes before the bus went over the cliff --

556
00:28:42,302 --> 00:28:44,457
last wednesday, 4:05 P.M.

557
00:28:44,508 --> 00:28:45,907
I was in new york on wednesday.

558
00:28:45,958 --> 00:28:47,067
Just got back this weekend.

559
00:28:47,118 --> 00:28:48,320
Hey, carla, sweetheart, come here.

560
00:28:49,852 --> 00:28:52,502
She's saying that bus-driver guy, the guy from the accident --

561
00:28:52,827 --> 00:28:54,068
he called here last week.

562
00:28:54,119 --> 00:28:54,723
Who?

563
00:28:54,774 --> 00:28:58,173
Ed doyle. Were you home last week between 4:00 and 5:00 P.M.?

564
00:28:58,802 --> 00:28:59,600
Yes.

565
00:29:00,409 --> 00:29:02,841
But I don't know what you're talking about.

566
00:29:03,433 --> 00:29:04,092
Wait.

567
00:29:05,134 --> 00:29:07,368
I did get a wrong number last week.

568
00:29:07,678 --> 00:29:09,345
It might have been wednesday.

569
00:29:13,507 --> 00:29:14,758
Thank you.
Sorry to bother you.

570
00:29:14,809 --> 00:29:15,525
No problem.

571
00:29:15,619 --> 00:29:16,653
Jessie, what's up?

572
00:29:16,969 --> 00:29:18,401
Jessie: You can stop whatever you're doing.

573
00:29:19,095 --> 00:29:19,859
Why?

574
00:29:20,004 --> 00:29:22,338
My father killed himself.

575
00:29:22,762 --> 00:29:25,685
The sheriff found his suicide note saved on his computer.

576
00:29:34,367 --> 00:29:35,820
How can you cry about him?

577
00:29:35,871 --> 00:29:37,714
You think he cared about either one of us?

578
00:29:38,132 --> 00:29:39,777
He left us with nothing!

579
00:29:39,828 --> 00:29:41,281
- Mom!
- What?!

580
00:29:43,263 --> 00:29:45,507
I think we can stop worr yingabout appearances.

581
00:29:47,279 --> 00:29:49,613
Hey, you know not to listen to her when she's like this, right?

582
00:29:50,214 --> 00:29:51,051
I don't know.

583
00:29:51,298 --> 00:29:52,326
Daddy was sick.

584
00:29:52,837 --> 00:29:54,595
He was in a lot of pain.

585
00:29:55,522 --> 00:29:57,576
Where -- where was it?

586
00:30:00,809 --> 00:30:03,240
It's hard to explain.

587
00:30:06,403 --> 00:30:08,384
Can I go play outside now?

588
00:30:09,025 --> 00:30:09,823
Yeah.

589
00:30:10,411 --> 00:30:11,825
Just stay in the yard, okay?

590
00:30:16,426 --> 00:30:20,895
Maybe he'll feel better when he's older, when he can read this.

591
00:30:21,366 --> 00:30:24,990
Sheriff was kind enough to print it out and fax it over.

592
00:30:28,056 --> 00:30:30,622
"I'm sorry to leave you this way,

593
00:30:30,972 --> 00:30:34,823
but I truly believe in my heart that it's for the best.

594
00:30:35,341 --> 00:30:36,836
I can't go on like this.

595
00:30:37,192 --> 00:30:39,082
I can't stay just for the kids.

596
00:30:39,512 --> 00:30:43,246
Even though they mean more to me than anything, this isn't good for them."

597
00:30:44,094 --> 00:30:45,806
You know, my mom was right for a change.

598
00:30:46,509 --> 00:30:47,703
Better off without him.

599
00:30:47,839 --> 00:30:48,645
Jessie.

600
00:31:10,799 --> 00:31:11,622
Slow night?

601
00:31:13,028 --> 00:31:13,799
Not bad.

602
00:31:14,481 --> 00:31:17,409
Busy enough to not get bored, slow enough to do my homework.

603
00:31:17,868 --> 00:31:20,172
I used to work nights at a store when I was in high school.

604
00:31:20,407 --> 00:31:21,204
Sweet gig.

605
00:31:22,725 --> 00:31:23,646
You go to Neptune high?

606
00:31:24,388 --> 00:31:25,064
Yeah.

607
00:31:25,531 --> 00:31:27,132
Ah, must be rough.

608
00:31:27,887 --> 00:31:29,706
Anyone close to you involved in that crash?

609
00:31:30,312 --> 00:31:31,117
No.

610
00:31:31,376 --> 00:31:32,718
Good. Thank god.

611
00:31:33,367 --> 00:31:35,005
Still, you probably knew some of the kids, right?

612
00:31:35,814 --> 00:31:36,778
You looking for a story?

613
00:31:39,492 --> 00:31:40,801
You got something?

614
00:31:41,529 --> 00:31:42,789
Can I see this for a minute?

615
00:31:47,385 --> 00:31:48,756
I've never seen notebooks like this.

616
00:31:49,347 --> 00:31:50,581
Reporters all use them --

617
00:31:51,037 --> 00:31:52,837
easy to hold and write at the same time.

618
00:31:53,787 --> 00:31:56,023
So, you said you knew some of the kids.

619
00:31:56,512 --> 00:31:57,352
No, I didn't.

620
00:32:02,115 --> 00:32:02,985
One quick question.

621
00:32:03,803 --> 00:32:05,997
If ed doyle dialed the wrong number,

622
00:32:06,048 --> 00:32:07,760
why was it a 4-minute call?

623
00:32:14,001 --> 00:32:17,944
I read his suicide note today, and I have a theory.

624
00:32:19,053 --> 00:32:22,548
He wasn't on planning on killing himself or a busload of kids.

625
00:32:22,914 --> 00:32:24,961
He was planning on leaving his wife --

626
00:32:25,640 --> 00:32:27,018
I'm guessing for you.

627
00:32:31,552 --> 00:32:32,450
Come in.

628
00:32:37,603 --> 00:32:39,572
Carla, this is jessie.

629
00:32:47,275 --> 00:32:48,654
You look just like your picture.

630
00:32:50,656 --> 00:32:52,267
That's why they call them "pictures."

631
00:32:53,792 --> 00:32:55,103
Your dad...

632
00:32:56,376 --> 00:32:59,054
talked about you all the time.

633
00:33:00,211 --> 00:33:00,943
Yeah.

634
00:33:01,186 --> 00:33:02,858
Sorry.
Can't say the same.

635
00:33:06,013 --> 00:33:09,057
We were in love, your dad and me.

636
00:33:09,745 --> 00:33:11,575
He called to say that he'd see me later.

637
00:33:11,626 --> 00:33:13,767
He didn't mean to drive that bus off a cliff.

638
00:33:14,584 --> 00:33:17,332
He just couldn't bring himself to leave you and your brother.

639
00:33:18,347 --> 00:33:20,406
He didn't want to leave you with your mother.

640
00:33:43,370 --> 00:33:46,656
Now I wish I was less understanding

641
00:33:47,841 --> 00:33:50,826
because I never really got to be with the man that I loved.

642
00:33:55,475 --> 00:33:58,704
You know the charge that goes up your spine at the moment of epiphany?

643
00:33:59,051 --> 00:33:59,981
It just hit me.

644
00:34:00,526 --> 00:34:02,626
I'm not going to let the list of things I want to do

645
00:34:02,677 --> 00:34:05,478
before I die turn into a list of regrets.

646
00:34:06,549 --> 00:34:07,295
You came.

647
00:34:09,760 --> 00:34:11,040
Oh, hey.

648
00:34:37,830 --> 00:34:39,203
What are you thinking?

649
00:34:41,851 --> 00:34:47,500
You know, I was trying to remember the over-under on the ohio state-texas game.

650
00:34:48,650 --> 00:34:49,558
Oh, god.

651
00:34:54,550 --> 00:34:55,153
What is that?

652
00:34:55,204 --> 00:34:55,804
Oh.

653
00:35:02,248 --> 00:35:04,265
Maybe we did it wrong.

654
00:35:06,893 --> 00:35:09,326
Uh, so, what's the protocol here?

655
00:35:09,649 --> 00:35:12,180
Do I bang my fist on the wall, call the front desk?

656
00:35:12,778 --> 00:35:14,532
Attempt to out-moan them?

657
00:35:16,129 --> 00:35:17,524
There's really only one thing to do.

658
00:35:23,458 --> 00:35:24,662
Spectra vision --

659
00:35:25,747 --> 00:35:26,917
loud.

660
00:35:47,758 --> 00:35:48,573
Hmm.

661
00:35:49,475 --> 00:35:50,858
What's different about you?

662
00:35:54,272 --> 00:35:55,409
Did you cut your hair or something?

663
00:35:58,922 --> 00:36:04,671
F.Y.I. -- If the cuddling is the best part, he didn't do it right.

664
00:36:20,275 --> 00:36:21,859
Neptune grand on fifth street.

665
00:36:25,091 --> 00:36:26,596
Room 1147, please.

666
00:36:28,877 --> 00:36:29,887
Hello?

667
00:36:32,898 --> 00:36:33,902
Hmm.

668
00:36:35,392 --> 00:36:36,573
Why didn't you wake me?

669
00:36:38,070 --> 00:36:42,635
I have about 15 minutes till my dad activates the homing device in my molar.

670
00:37:10,433 --> 00:37:14,666
Make sure you really clean that up, because if we get bugs, I'm gonna be pissed.

671
00:37:38,092 --> 00:37:39,895
Hey, keith, you looking for me?

672
00:37:40,003 --> 00:37:40,680
I am.

673
00:37:40,731 --> 00:37:43,075
All right. Good.
Hit me with some good news.

674
00:37:51,304 --> 00:37:54,411
I appreciate the offer, woody, but I've decided not to run.

675
00:37:54,723 --> 00:37:55,355
No.

676
00:37:56,151 --> 00:37:58,469
Good luck with the election, and you can count on my vote.

677
00:37:59,086 --> 00:38:00,614
You change your mind, you give me a call.

678
00:38:01,861 --> 00:38:03,420
I feel pretty good about the decision.

679
00:38:03,901 --> 00:38:04,805
Fair enough.

680
00:38:05,880 --> 00:38:07,279
You take good care, keith.

681
00:38:07,399 --> 00:38:08,457
Always a pleasure.

682
00:38:08,508 --> 00:38:09,111
All right.

683
00:38:12,042 --> 00:38:14,331
Just listen to me for two seconds.
I've been here for three hours.

684
00:38:14,382 --> 00:38:16,851
Talk to me for one minute.
My father did not kill himself.

685
00:38:17,295 --> 00:38:19,020
We have the note.
We have the physical evidence.

686
00:38:19,071 --> 00:38:20,931
- The case is closed.
- Open it back up.

687
00:38:20,982 --> 00:38:22,337
That wasn't a suicide note.

688
00:38:22,503 --> 00:38:25,056
He was leaving my mom for another woman.
I have proof.

689
00:38:25,754 --> 00:38:26,340
Listen to me.

690
00:38:26,340 --> 00:38:28,779
You have to give another press conference, okay?

691
00:38:28,916 --> 00:38:31,590
Please! I have a little brother.
He's 8.

692
00:38:31,641 --> 00:38:34,198
He needs to know that my father didn't kill those kids.

693
00:38:34,462 --> 00:38:36,259
Sorry about your loss.
The case is closed.

694
00:38:44,425 --> 00:38:45,385
What are we doing?

695
00:38:46,163 --> 00:38:47,570
Exercising patience.

696
00:38:49,601 --> 00:38:50,590
Just wait for it.

697
00:38:53,341 --> 00:38:54,600
Wait for it and go.

698
00:38:55,671 --> 00:38:57,701
Wait. She's the one?

699
00:38:57,939 --> 00:38:59,106
My plan is unfolding.

700
00:39:00,113 --> 00:39:02,042
Let's just be impressed, watch it play out.

701
00:39:02,362 --> 00:39:04,646
- Thanks, but I got it from here.
- Whoa, whoa.

702
00:39:05,053 --> 00:39:07,782
Do you want your dad to hear you got into a catfight the first week of school?

703
00:39:08,994 --> 00:39:10,254
You have my spark plugs?

704
00:39:10,453 --> 00:39:11,898
You have your insurance information?

705
00:39:15,096 --> 00:39:16,414
Paper bag, backseat.

706
00:39:25,345 --> 00:39:26,331
Thank you.

707
00:39:28,421 --> 00:39:30,835
Chances of her knowing how to replace a spark plug?

708
00:39:31,245 --> 00:39:33,529
Chances of me running into her in the girls' locker room

709
00:39:33,580 --> 00:39:35,528
and unleashing my own brand of justice?

710
00:39:35,624 --> 00:39:36,719
Slim. She doesn't go here.

711
00:39:37,120 --> 00:39:38,022
She's a reporter.

712
00:39:38,518 --> 00:39:40,249
Think Drew Barrymore in "never been kissed."

713
00:39:40,886 --> 00:39:42,829
Hey, if Drew's in it, I've seen it.

714
00:39:43,303 --> 00:39:45,422
I let Clemmons know we had an imposter on campus.

715
00:39:46,749 --> 00:39:48,100
Oh, another thing you should know about me --

716
00:39:48,338 --> 00:39:52,019
I like my gratitude in small doses, spread out over time.

717
00:40:03,580 --> 00:40:06,586
I may have to reconsider my stand on nice guys.

718
00:40:12,511 --> 00:40:14,980
Um, who was that kissing you?

719
00:40:15,517 --> 00:40:16,808
That was jackie.

720
00:40:18,028 --> 00:40:18,770
Oh.

721
00:40:29,713 --> 00:40:30,430
Hey.

722
00:40:32,513 --> 00:40:34,509
How did woody goodman take the news?

723
00:40:34,777 --> 00:40:35,766
Pretty well, actually.

724
00:40:36,550 --> 00:40:37,458
He wasn't bummed?

725
00:40:37,711 --> 00:40:38,392
Nope.

726
00:40:39,466 --> 00:40:40,329
Then he's crazy.

727
00:40:40,747 --> 00:40:41,927
I told him I'm running.

728
00:40:42,365 --> 00:40:43,491
Oh, my god!

729
00:40:44,156 --> 00:40:45,168
Oh, that's great.

730
00:40:45,729 --> 00:40:46,595
That's great.

731
00:40:47,024 --> 00:40:48,306
I feel safer already.

732
00:40:52,886 --> 00:40:53,767
What?

733
00:40:54,639 --> 00:40:56,128
You look different, that's all.

734
00:40:57,357 --> 00:41:01,628
Okay, I know my father is a brilliant detective with a keen intuition

735
00:41:01,679 --> 00:41:07,357
